                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1643</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-13T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1915, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 14, 12.15 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2726. Consular agent Swinemünde reports that every American vessel passing
                    Drogden lightship will be stopped by a German war vessel and brought to
                    Swinemünde for examination, whether or not it carries contraband. What
                    disposition does Department desire to have the consular agent make of masters’
                    protests?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
